why don t i dream sometimes when i sleep i don t dream is this normal and why don t i dream you do dream basically you go through rem every minutes during a normal night of sleep we usually experience about or periods of rem sleep they are quite short at the beginning of the night and longer at the end it is common to wake for a short time at the end of a rem phase it is during the rem phase that you go from deep sleep to a lighter sleep if you wake up you remember your dream if you are dreaming between rem and don't wake up you may not remember your dreams but everyone dreams some of us may sleep lighter than others so reaching rem is practically waking us up i always dream always remember and mostly get woken up by my dreams Dream Sleep Lucid dreaming Turiya R.E.M. (band) Electroencephalography Nightmare Sleep disorder Philosophical skepticism Hypnagogia Siesta Jon Secada Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Urinary incontinence Passenger car Cliff Richard STS-60 Reality Dream (DC Comics) Haibane Renmei Comment Little Nemo Delayed sleep phase syndrome Freddy's Dead: The Final Nightmare Telepathy Muraqaba Finnegans Wake Emotions (album) Futurama (TV series - season 5) 50 First Dates Knots Landing Shaggy dog story Fertility awareness Nightwish Dreamlands Radiation poisoning American Idiot The Amber Spyglass Daylight saving time Ionizing radiation Raphe nuclei Hypnosis Adamawa Province Sleep and learning Mandukya Upanishad Gemini 7 The Shining (film) Phantasms (TNG episode) Mattress A Day in the Life The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Daz Dillinger Cannabis (drug) Sleep apnea Saga (band) Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Characters of The Sandman Umbra (World of Darkness) Sleep deprivation Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Sleeping Murder Cetacean intelligence Waylon Jennings Canonical hours Slow Train Coming Histamine Epilepsy Under Milk Wood Norwegian Wood (This Bird Has Flown) Castle of the Winds World Fantasy Award for Best Novel Fleetwood Mac Night Wake Me Up 